<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="158" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                                    </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d158fn1">The source text is marked
                                        “copy”.</note>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">immediate</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-30">December 30
                                            [1941.]</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>Following for President from Prime Minister.</p>
                                <p>Naturally both the declaration and the Unity Plan, having to be
                                    referred to so many different parts will require final review by
                                    us on Thursday afternoon. Meanwhile as I am out of touch I hope
                                    you will discuss outstanding minor points on declaration with
                                    Halifax, and points raised by H. M. Government on Unity Plan
                                    with Pound after they have been considered by our (Mission?). In
                                    principle, everything seems settled, but I expect it will take
                                    till the end of week <pb facs="0360" n="286" xml:id="pg_286"/>
                                    to get final fair copies. This will be a pretty considerable
                                    achievement.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>